metadata.name: Zhu(竹) #25
metadata.description:
Zhu(竹):

"Zhu" is a series of 100 oriental abstract pieces featuring the imagery of bamboo, a symbol of integrity and strength in traditional Chinese culture.

Zhu's generative system is an exploration of this cultural symbol by modern art language. Elements of the paintings are merely circles, enclosed flow field shapes, and the blank space behind these visual objects. Blank-leaving is intentionally applied at various degrees throughout the series. The vast empty space beyond the plants is open to and embraces every kind of interpretation.

Zhu's outputs span hours of the day from dawn to dusk to night. Its color schemes explored four styles from traditional to modern. The simple yet complex senses and feelings reflected are surprisingly versatile.

metadata.name: The Light of Summer #28
metadata.description:
Description of Seasons of Siskiyou Series
Surrounding my home, covering more than one million acres, is the Rogue River - Siskiyou National Forest which takes up three southern Oregon counties and one northern California county. It’s a magical place that fills the imagination and lifts the spirit; a place that inspires with its uniqueness, its legends, and its larger-than-life vistas.

Each season in the Siskiyou mountains is a unique experience unto itself. So, with an attention to the feelings this place evokes at any given time of the year, I designed four generative tokens to create an impression of the emotion–the calming quietness; the peaceful solitude; the overwhelming contrasts and variety of forms, shapes and textures; the magic and playful mystery; the welcomingness and foreboding. These four works feature clever and inventive creative coding techniques in a rich, graphic style to craft a stunning impression of the Seasons of Siskiyou.


Token 2 of 4 - THE LIGHT OF SUMMER (1990 x 1080) p5js Generative Token.
After weeks of a lengthening day, the color of spring gives way to the light of summer.  The air glows with the warmth of an apex sun; the coolness of the shadows welcomes tiny denizens; golden hues of drying flora frame the brilliance of lingering blooms.  Magic sails in solar breezes lazily drifting along with the whims of daylight.  Hike along remote trails, lose yourself in the unique beauty, and be immersed in the Light of Summer.

Output and Coding Features of “The Light of Summer”:

The Light of Summer features a variety of recursive algorithms to generate a range of plant forms.  The flowers are created with skewable vectored-ellipses to provide depth.  The output is generated by layering various generative systems using a one-point perspective.  An optical effect is applied to create atmosphere and accent-textures.  A radial gradient sets the background and frames the scene with a sense of atmosphere and humidity. 

Press DOWN ARROW to save the output as a png image file.

Each iteration varies the color palette, shape and density of the vegetation, the position and density of flowers and the optical-effect texture.

Token Published April 21, 2022 on FXHASH set at 75 Editions.
Written and designed by Ed Cavett using the p5js library.
Token 2 of 4 from the series “The Seasons of Siskiyou.”

metadata.name: (un)existing #80
metadata.description:
The existing nature grows on the unexisting spirits.

Generative sketch, based on the pen and ink drawings of Po Sheng Chen. Po Sheng Chen is an Architect who has drawn nothing but Architecture for over 25 years. He tried to explore something different from his previous style (Brutalism with Magical Realism), so developed his own Minimalist Architecture process and style. After breaking up all the complicated elements and symbols, he chose a simple and naive way to present “pure volumes in the space (the essential of Architecture)”: the Use of different densities of vertical lines to create different faces of volumes, with the addition of horizontal lines to create shadows on the volumes. Shadow determined the form of volumes, then they became a clear composition in the space, Eliminating chaos. These lines seem like spirits to Po Sheng Chen, because they represent the soul of Architecture, but they do not have a specific form or meaning...they are between existing and unexisting! Tezumie is a creative generative artist. He saw the latest experimental drawings of Po Sheng Chen, and after reaching out, the collab was formed with the goal of creating a digital representation of the original concept surrounded by a natural and overgrown environment. The combination of nature and architecture.

Made in p5js.

metadata.name: Reconnaissance #266
metadata.description:
An immense quiet accompanies a sense of looming futility while peering down across vast new worlds. What use is there in discovering and documenting these unknown places? Who would care to seek out lifeless lands lost in the cosmos?

Any civilization capable of such reconnaissance might seem above the little hope that barren lands may bring. Unless, of course, there is a hope of answering the most desperate of needs: Finding a New Home.

Were these images captured by humans on Earth, or on Mars, or somewhere even further away in distance and probability? Maybe they’re recon from another planet’s civilization — one that shares our struggle to find true harmony with the world they have.

Inspired by the remarkable satellite imagery in the compendium “This is Mars,” Reconnaissance suggests what may lie outside our habitable lands — and that we risk missing what's already here while being compelled to look further and further for what’s next.


Choose a resolution (1-6) by adding "&scale=4" to the URL in live view.
Created with p5.js

TENDER x Nat Sarkissian
May 2022

metadata.name: stigmergy #35
metadata.description:
Stigmergy is a method of decentralized organization in which agents communicate by leaving traces in a shared environment. This piece simulates a kind of stigmergy among a large population of particles. Each particle leaves a trail behind it as it moves, and determines its direction of motion based on the trails around it. The rules for how a particle should move based on its surroundings were created with a user-guided evolutionary process.

Press "c" to capture a 2048x2048 image of the simulation. You can also press the spacebar to pause/unpause the simulation, and press "n" while paused to move the simulation forward a single step.

metadata.name: Visa to the stars #406
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: intentions 01 #74
metadata.description:
A 3D map of an imaginary cavern is created with Perlin noise; this is sliced in to an arbitrary stack, and each slice is rendered as a dot field. This is, in turn, displayed on the screen as a rotating isometric cube. Along the bottom, one can see the total number of slices, and the gradient created by the two colors used.

Traits: 

Color 1 & Color 2: each chosen from a single pool of 10. Each color is equally likely, so the least likely result is two of the same color. 

Resolution: This is the resolution of the dot field, and describes the complexity. Three possible results, with 1 being the least likely.

Slices: The number of slices in the stack, with 5 being the least likely. 

Created in p5.js

metadata.name: Fleur des Sinus #67
metadata.description:
Originally based on Alberto Burri's 1973- 1976 Screen Prints, then further iterated upon: Fleur des Sinus is meant to play with abstraction by designing larger than the canvas. Creating something that's clearly defined and pushing in just enough to find new compositions in section and intersection.

There are two possible modes, changing the shape of the flowers.
26 palettes are available, each composed of 4 colors: 104 colors in total.
A palette is picked for each edge flower, the center flower expresses itself with no inhibitions.
The Flowers are made up of between 4-10 petals.
The background pattern is 1-6 petal minimal dot flower patterns.

Press 's' to save the image in Live View.
